Starting from the 29th of May, 2021 until the 9th of June, 2021 the Cyprus government enforced the following orders: 
Movements are prohibited from 01.00 a.m. to 05.00 a.m. with the exception of the following cases:      
 (i) going to and coming back from the workplace, as well as for work purposes, by using the Confirmation of Employee’s Movement attached hereto as Annex;      
 (ii) going to a medical center or hospital or pharmacy of a veterinarian for medical emergencies;    
(iii) provision of urgent assistance to persons who are unable to take care of themselves or who must protect themselves;      
(iv) representatives of political parties, candidate MPs, observers of the Organization for Security and Co-operation in Europe, as well as any other person for the purposes of the electoral procedure of the parliamentary elections of 30 May 2021: provided that people should carry their identity card or passport in case of control by the competent authorities.

Starting from March 1, 2021 until March 15, 2021 the Cyprus Government enforced the following orders: 

Retailers:  

(i) should observe the measure of 1 person per 10 sqm of working capacity for shops below 1,000 sqm and of 1 person per 15 sqm of working capacity for shops exceeding 1,000 sqm. Moreover, big stores exceeding 1,000 sqm are obliged to ensure that there is a check at the entrance in the presence of an authorized person so that the maximum number of customers is upheld;   

 (ii) moreover, they should take measures to mark the minimum distance of 2 meters, which should be observed by the customers while they are being served, both inside and outside the premises and display at the entrance of the premises the maximum number of persons permitted in the premises under the guidelines issued by the Ministry of Health and the Ministry of Labour, Welfare and Social Insurance;

Starting from March 1, 2021 until March 15, 2021 the Cyprus Government enforced the following orders: 

-The operation of swimming pools is suspended other than for therapeutic exercise of persons with disabilities or for training of persons falling within the provision of paragraph (au), subject to the guidelines of the Ministry of Health and the Cyprus Sports Organisation;  -The operation of gyms, dancing schools and other sports academies is suspended other than for sports activities under the provisions of paragraph (au) and subject to the guidelines of the Ministry of Health and the Cyprus Sports Organisation;   
-The operation of archaeological sites, museums and historic sites, visual art places and galleries is permitted subject to the guidelines of the Ministry of Health.         
-The operation of itinerant sales and bazaars is permitted subject to possession of the relevant authorisation by the competent Municipal or Community authority and subject to the guidelines of the Ministry of Health;     
- The operation of hairdressing salons, barber shops, beauty centres and tattooing shops is permitted subject to the guidelines of the Ministry of Health;    
-The operation of night clubs, event venues, discos, clubs and music and dancing venues is suspended; 
